appearances.snippet: . >> i yield 1.5 minutes to the gentlewoman from wisconsin, congresswoman gwen moore. >> the gentlewoman is recognized. >> thank you so very, very much. the gentlelady from alabama. mr. speaker, i rise today to urge my colleagues to vote in support of renewing the african growth and opportunity act. agoa is a critical program to advance prosperity for the people of sub-saharan africa and to maintain united states leadership in the region. it's a program that has bipartisan support. agoa is far from perfect, and so i understand concerns raised by a wide range of stakeholders, including labor, environmental and other trade groups, about proposed changes to make this program better, stronger and more effective moving forward. this is a straight authorization reauthorization for three years, providing a runway for all stakeholders to weigh in on needed improvements to appropriate the sage words of frederick douglas. power concedes nothing without a demand. it never has, and it never will. the us must not cede power to china or any other world power by not curing the lapse of this vital soft
